sif3.infra.rest.env
Class ProviderEnvironmentManager

java.lang.Object
  sif3.infra.rest.env.BaseEnvironmentManager
      sif3.infra.rest.env.ProviderEnvironmentManager

public class ProviderEnvironmentManager
extends BaseEnvironmentManager

This class deals with the main functions relating to the environments that need to be managed on a provider. It is a cut down version of an Environment Provider and is required for DIRECT environments on the provider side. It deals with the main functions of a environment provider as defined in the SIF3 spec. Only lower level classes in this framework really require this class, mainly the resources for objects as well as the actual environment resource.

Author:
Joerg Huber

createEnvironment

public sif3.infra.common.model.EnvironmentType createEnvironment(sif3.infra.common.model.EnvironmentType inputEnvironment,
                                                                 java.lang.String userName,
                                                                 java.lang.String password,
                                                                 javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType mediaType)
This method will create an environment for a consumer. The environment will be created based on the given input environment information. If this operation fails an error is logged and null is returned. The environment will be created and all the information according to the SIF3 spec is returned (i.e. Session Token, Environment Id etc).

Parameters:
inputEnvironment - The basic information required by the environment provider to create the environment for the consumer.
userName - Initial user name for environment creation.
password - Initial password for environment creation. Is used to create the new AuthenticationToken.
mediaType - Indicates if the consumer is using XML or JSON.
Returns:
See desc.

loadEnvironmentByAuthToken

public sif3.infra.common.model.EnvironmentType loadEnvironmentByAuthToken(java.lang.String authToken)
This method will load an environment from the environment store. This is used to get an environment rather than creating one. If no environment for the given authentication token exists in the environment store then null is returned.

Parameters:
authToken - The authorisation token based on which the environment shall be returned.
Returns:
See desc.
